(b) The Will of Gool shewn in what hc commands is the Rule of our Conscience. When God has by commands and prohibitions shewn what he wishes us to do and not to do, it is our business to accommodate our Wills to his Will. The simple Rule is, that we are to will what. Grod wills that we should will. Thus when God commanded Abraham to sacrifice Isaac, he was bound to be willing to do it3 though, as appeared, it was not the Will of God that it should really be done.
